This paper deals with the security of power systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to learn relationships between different parts of the power system, which suggests that it could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the vulnerability of power systems to attacks, which could fall under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper uses optimization techniques to evaluate the worst-case consequences of attacks, which could fall under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
